It is found in Indonesia and Malaysia, where it is found in Sumatra, Java and northern montane areas of Borneo.
Its natural habitat is tropical moist submontane montane forests between 900m to 3000m, where it is a common to fairly common species.', descrizione_fonte = 'Wikipedia (en)', descrizione_url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indigo_flycatcher' where nome_scientifico = 'Eumyias indigo' and descrizione is null;
update specie set descrizione = 'The turquoise flycatcher, also known as the island flycatcher, is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae. It is found in Indonesia and the Philippines. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests.', descrizione_fonte = 'Wikipedia (en)', descrizione_url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turquoise_flycatcher' where nome_scientifico = 'Eumyias panayensis' and descrizione is null;
update specie set descrizione = 'The verditer flycatcher is an Old World flycatcher It is found from the Himalayas through Southeast Asia to Sumatra. This species is named after its distinctive shade of copper-sulphate blue and has a dark patch between the eyes and above the bill base. The adult males are intense blue on all areas of the body, except for the black eye-patch and grey vent. Adult females and sub-adults are lighter blue.', descrizione_fonte = 'Wikipedia (en)', descrizione_url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Verditer_flycatcher' where nome_scientifico = 'Eumyias thalassinus' and descrizione is null;
