It is found in eastern Indonesia and New Guinea. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest and subtropical or tropical mangrove forest.', descrizione_fonte = 'Wikipedia (en)', descrizione_url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_sunbird' where nome_scientifico = 'Leptocoma aspasia' and descrizione is null;
update specie set descrizione = 'The copper-throated sunbird  is a small passerine within the Nectariniidae family. They sustain themselves by consuming nectar as well as small invertebrates. As a member of the Nectariniidae family, they possess downward curved beaks and have pectoral tufts of yellow feathers. They are found in south-eastern Asia, predominantly in coastal regions.', descrizione_fonte = 'Wikipedia (en)', descrizione_url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copper-throated_sunbird' where nome_scientifico = 'Leptocoma calcostetha' and descrizione is null;
update specie set descrizione = 'The crimson-backed sunbird or small sunbird is a sunbird endemic to the Western Ghats of India. Like other sunbirds, they feed mainly on nectar although they take insects, especially to feed their young. They are tiny birds that are resident and are found in forests but are particularly attracted to gardens at the edge of the forest where people grow suitable flower-bearing plants. They usually perch while taking nectar.', descrizione_fonte = 'Wikipedia (en)', descrizione_url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crimson-backed_sunbird' where nome_scientifico = 'Leptocoma minima' and descrizione is null;
update specie set descrizione = 'The purple-throated sunbird, is a species of bird in the family Nectariniidae. 
