It is found in Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Myanmar, and Thailand.
Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests.', descrizione_fonte = 'Wikipedia (en)', descrizione_url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ferruginous_babbler' where nome_scientifico = 'Pellorneum bicolor' and descrizione is null;
update specie set descrizione = 'The Javan black-capped babbler is a species of bird in the family Pellorneidae.
It is endemic to the island of Java in Indonesia. The Malayan black-capped babbler and the Bornean black-capped babbler were both formerly considered conspecific, but were split from it in 2021.
Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest.', descrizione_fonte = 'Wikipedia (en)', descrizione_url = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javan_black-capped_babbler' where nome_scientifico = 'Pellorneum capistratum' and descrizione is null;
